OL,3,CLeasehold flats are being banned by
OL,4,Cthe government - what does it mean for
OL,5,Cyou?
OL,7,FGovernment proposals, published on
OL,8,FMonday, will scrap the current system,
OL,9,Funder which third-party landlords can
OL,10,Fown the lease of a building, therefore
OL,11,Fmaking decisions on behalf of
OL,12,Fhomeowners.
OL,14,FLeasehold will be replaced with
OL,15,Fcommonhold, an ownership structure
OL,16,Fthat allows people to own and manage
OL,17,Ftheir buildings jointly.
