OL,3,CLeasehold flats are being banned by
OL,4,Cthe government - what does it mean for
OL,5,Cyou?
OL,7,FIf you own a leasehold property, you
OL,8,Fown the property but not the building
OL,9,For the land the property is built on,
OL,10,Fand have to pay ground rent to a third-
OL,11,Fparty landlord, on top of service
OL,12,Fcharge to maintain the building.
OL,14,FWhen you buy a leasehold property, you
OL,15,Fpurchase the right to live in it for a
OL,16,Fset number of years. Leasehold
OL,17,Fproperties are normally flats or
OL,18,Fapartments in larger buildings.
