OL,3,CLeasehold flats are being banned by
OL,4,Cthe government - what does it mean for
OL,5,Cyou?
OL,7,FMany people in leasehold properties
OL,8,Fsay they have no control over the
OL,9,Fcosts, which often increase after the
OL,10,Fproperty is bought. Campaigners say
OL,11,Fpeople often end up stuck in houses
OL,12,Fthey can't afford to keep living in
OL,13,Fbecause of rising ground rent and
OL,14,Fservice charge, also making it
OL,15,Fdifficult to sell the property.
OL,17,FThe new plans will also include a ban
OL,18,Fon the sale of new leasehold flats.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/10
